WEBVTT

00:41.501 --> 00:44.087
(ice cubes clinking)

00:45.797 --> 00:47.882
(page turning)

00:47.966 --> 00:49.092
(marker draws line on paper)

00:49.259 --> 00:53.888
(ice cubes clinking)

00:55.974 --> 00:58.685
WOMAN:
I swear she's older than my mom.

00:58.852 --> 01:00.979
Fucking kill me if I'm
still doing this at her age.

01:03.481 --> 01:06.359
Kill you now
if you ask me nicely.

01:08.486 --> 01:10.256
You know we're not allowed
to eat or drink in here.

01:10.280 --> 01:11.280
Yeah.

01:11.364 --> 01:13.491
Oh, fuck off.

01:13.575 --> 01:15.243
MAN: What did you say?

01:15.326 --> 01:18.121
Uh, I believe I said,
"Oh, fuck off."

01:19.456 --> 01:20.582
MAN: Pack up.

01:23.668 --> 01:25.128
I'm almost finished

01:25.211 --> 01:26.963
- with this document.
- Now.

01:29.299 --> 01:30.467
(sighs)

01:44.063 --> 01:45.523
(slurping)

01:47.859 --> 01:49.027
(ice cubes clatter)

01:54.699 --> 01:58.787
(slow music playing)

01:58.953 --> 02:02.999
(siren wailing)

02:09.422 --> 02:13.843
<i>♪ I thought of you last night ♪</i>

02:14.844 --> 02:18.264
<i>♪ I thought of you
and thought of you ♪</i>

02:18.348 --> 02:22.685
<i>♪ Until the morning light ♪</i>

02:22.769 --> 02:26.481
<i>♪ And I couldn't sleep
and I couldn't sleep ♪</i>

02:26.564 --> 02:28.066
Ugh.

02:28.149 --> 02:31.611
<i>♪ Last night ♪</i>

02:33.905 --> 02:38.409
<i>♪ I wanted you last night ♪</i>

02:38.493 --> 02:43.248
<i>♪ I wanted you and wanted you ♪</i>

02:43.331 --> 02:45.083
(exhales)

02:45.166 --> 02:48.169
- (truck approaching)
- (man shouting in distance)

02:48.253 --> 02:53.758
- (truck reverse alert beeping)
- (shouting continues)

02:55.426 --> 02:57.554
(silverware clatters)

03:01.975 --> 03:03.017
(sighs)

03:03.184 --> 03:04.394
Psst-psst.

03:05.728 --> 03:07.438
Come on.

03:10.400 --> 03:11.609
(sighs)

03:12.360 --> 03:13.695
(cat meows)

03:16.614 --> 03:18.741
Since when did you get picky?

03:18.825 --> 03:19.826
Hmm?

03:20.869 --> 03:21.911
(cat sneezes)

03:23.705 --> 03:24.873
(sighs)

03:28.585 --> 03:33.006
<i>♪ Bring your love to me,
bring your love to me ♪</i>

03:33.172 --> 03:37.051
<i>♪ Tonight ♪</i>

03:41.639 --> 03:42.640
MAN: Hey, taxi!

03:50.106 --> 03:52.734
(shivering)

03:56.529 --> 03:58.239
(upbeat music playing)

03:58.323 --> 04:00.491
(indistinct chatter)

04:07.415 --> 04:09.083
WOMAN: Oh, thank you.

04:13.087 --> 04:15.673
TOM CLANCY:
But then there was nobody left,

04:15.757 --> 04:19.260
and I was standing by myself.

04:19.344 --> 04:21.529
WOMAN 2: And how long until
your next book will come out?

04:21.553 --> 04:23.681
TOM: Good question. Uh...

04:23.765 --> 04:25.683
Well, this is a surprise.

04:25.767 --> 04:27.769
You invited me, did you not?

04:27.852 --> 04:29.604
You didn't reply.

04:29.687 --> 04:31.230
Coat check?

04:31.314 --> 04:33.691
At my party, we just threw
the coats on the bed.

04:34.692 --> 04:36.235
Good to see you, too, Lee.

04:36.319 --> 04:38.738
You never called me back,
and I...

04:38.821 --> 04:40.698
I have new ideas.

04:40.782 --> 04:42.200
Is this why you came?

04:43.242 --> 04:45.578
- Yeah.
- Well, I'm glad you're here.

04:45.662 --> 04:46.788
Try to have a good time.

04:46.955 --> 04:50.416
TOM: I like interviews.
Don't get me wrong.

04:50.500 --> 04:54.796
I just wish that you could
get it all done at once.

04:54.879 --> 04:56.714
(Woman 2 laughing)

05:04.847 --> 05:06.033
WOMAN 3:
Did you read it? It was...

05:06.057 --> 05:07.767
TOM: I haven't missed
a day of writing

05:07.850 --> 05:10.311
for the past 25 years.

05:10.395 --> 05:12.313
WOMAN 2: And do you ever
have trouble beginning?

05:12.397 --> 05:15.692
I don't subscribe to
the notion of writer's block.

05:15.775 --> 05:17.485
You never experience it?

05:17.568 --> 05:18.736
Writer's block is a term

05:18.820 --> 05:20.571
invented by the
writing community

05:20.738 --> 05:22.615
- to justify their laziness.
- (women chuckle)

05:22.782 --> 05:23.842
My success
is nothing more than

05:23.866 --> 05:25.466
that I have the determination
and stamina

05:25.535 --> 05:27.328
to sit and get the work done.

05:27.495 --> 05:29.998
- It's simple.
- Jackass.

05:30.164 --> 05:32.417
KAREN:
I mean, I find his distaste

05:32.500 --> 05:35.336
for linear plot structure
downright macabre.

05:37.088 --> 05:38.088
(sighs)

05:58.651 --> 06:00.987
Well, that was quick.
Did you get properly fed?

06:01.070 --> 06:02.947
This week,
will you return my call?

06:03.031 --> 06:05.033
Sure. We'll see.

06:05.116 --> 06:07.577
I'm working on a lot
of fascinating projects.

06:07.660 --> 06:10.580
I just need my agent
to call me back.

06:10.663 --> 06:12.248
I don't think the world
is waiting

06:12.331 --> 06:14.709
for another Fanny Brice
biography, Lee.

06:14.792 --> 06:16.127
And we may disagree

06:16.210 --> 06:18.755
on what is considered
fascinating.

06:19.756 --> 06:20.756
Good night.

06:21.674 --> 06:24.177
Why do you have mostly-used
toilet paper rolls

06:24.260 --> 06:25.720
in the cabinet in your bathroom?

06:27.263 --> 06:29.724
So that the guests
can have a full roll.

06:30.641 --> 06:32.560
Well, that's batshit, Marjorie.

06:43.488 --> 06:46.491
I lost my ticket,
but that's my coat over there.

06:46.574 --> 06:48.367
There on the end.

06:53.122 --> 06:55.249
Have a good night, ma'am.

07:11.474 --> 07:12.642
(door closes)

07:19.398 --> 07:21.317
WOMAN (on TV):
<i>You'll be a very rich man.</i>

07:21.400 --> 07:23.111
<i>(indistinct chatter on TV)</i>

07:33.121 --> 07:34.640
REGINA: <i>We'll talk about
it in a few years.</i>

07:34.664 --> 07:36.999
OSCAR:
<i>I want to talk about it now!</i>

07:37.083 --> 07:38.560
LEE (as Regina): There are lots
of things to consider.

07:38.584 --> 07:40.002
After all,
they are first cousins.

07:40.294 --> 07:41.688
(as Oscar)
Well, that's not unusual,

07:41.712 --> 07:43.607
our grandmother and grandfather
were first cousins.

07:43.631 --> 07:45.133
(as Regina)
Yes, and look at us.

07:45.216 --> 07:46.384
(Lee and Regina laugh)

07:48.219 --> 07:49.220
(laughs)

07:51.973 --> 07:53.724
Here, Jersey girl.

07:53.808 --> 07:56.811
I brought your favorite.
I brought you shrimpy.

07:56.894 --> 07:58.604
Hmm? Come on.
It's your favorite.

08:01.774 --> 08:06.487
REGINA: <i>Very well. I assure you,
Oscar, I will think about it...</i>

08:08.739 --> 08:10.867
(dogs barking)

08:12.660 --> 08:15.580
So, you still have a balance,
Miss Israel.

08:15.663 --> 08:17.665
Yeah, I'm aware of that.

08:17.748 --> 08:21.544
But she's really sick
and she's very old.

08:21.627 --> 08:23.212
I'm sorry,
but the doctor told me that

08:23.296 --> 08:24.731
I need to have at least
half the balance

08:24.755 --> 08:26.132
before I do any tests.

08:27.925 --> 08:29.969
Didn't you people take
a Hippocratic oath?

08:30.136 --> 08:32.513
You owe us $82.

08:32.597 --> 08:34.890
God. Wow.

08:42.732 --> 08:44.525
(Jersey sneezing)

08:44.609 --> 08:46.652
You know, if she did come
out here, she'd see this.

08:52.992 --> 08:55.411
All right, I have $14.

08:55.578 --> 08:57.788
I'm sorry, but I can't.

09:00.374 --> 09:01.751
No, we need half the balance.

09:10.134 --> 09:11.844
(car horn honks in distance)

09:21.270 --> 09:22.563
God...

09:22.647 --> 09:23.731
Asshole.

09:35.326 --> 09:37.453
Okay. Just these.

09:39.038 --> 09:42.250
Come on, man. I schlepped
these all the way here.

09:42.333 --> 09:43.960
I'll give you two dollars.

09:44.043 --> 09:45.962
I don't want the others.

09:46.045 --> 09:47.380
I don't even need that much.

09:47.463 --> 09:49.674
I just don't want to carry
them around anymore.

09:49.882 --> 09:51.592
I got a sick cat, and I...

09:51.676 --> 09:53.427
I told you
I don't want the others.

09:53.511 --> 09:55.221
There's people waiting.

09:55.304 --> 09:58.057
You know, you don't have
to be so disrespectful.

09:58.140 --> 10:00.601
Okay? You have actually
carried my books here.

10:01.894 --> 10:02.895
And you are?

10:03.104 --> 10:05.147
I'm Lee Israel.

10:05.231 --> 10:07.858
Oh, Miss Israel.
We have copies

10:07.942 --> 10:09.735
of your latest work
right over there.

10:13.406 --> 10:14.699
You're a rude little ape.

10:14.782 --> 10:15.783
Okay, get your garbage

10:15.866 --> 10:17.368
- off my counter.
- No!

10:30.089 --> 10:32.300
(door opens)

10:32.967 --> 10:34.760
- Miss Israel?
- Hi, Andrei.

10:34.969 --> 10:36.470
It's been three months.

10:36.554 --> 10:38.806
I know. I'm sorry.
I'm working on it.

10:38.889 --> 10:40.474
I don't want to call
the management.

10:41.684 --> 10:44.770
Can you just cut me
a little slack? I'm...

10:44.854 --> 10:47.648
going through a rough patch,
and I just lost my job.

10:47.732 --> 10:49.567
I think it was ageism.

10:49.650 --> 10:51.235
You've been here
longer than I have,

10:51.319 --> 10:53.696
and you've been
kind to my mother.

10:55.114 --> 10:57.533
Just get it to me soon.
I will.

10:57.616 --> 10:59.368
Absolutely. Thank you.

11:01.746 --> 11:03.664
Uh, hey, in the meantime,

11:03.748 --> 11:05.624
do you think you could send
an exterminator

11:05.708 --> 11:07.126
up to my apartment?

11:07.209 --> 11:09.545
I have an untenable
fly situation.

11:17.428 --> 11:18.763
(sighing)

11:23.768 --> 11:24.977
(sighs)

11:28.773 --> 11:30.775
(soft music playing)

11:30.858 --> 11:35.154
<i>♪ I'll take Manhattan ♪</i>

11:36.530 --> 11:38.366
Good afternoon, darling.

11:38.449 --> 11:40.451
MAN: Hey, Jack Handsome.

11:40.534 --> 11:42.078
Can I have a beer,
pretty please?

11:42.244 --> 11:43.954
I don't know. Can you?

11:50.920 --> 11:52.922
- Lee Israel?
- (loud slam)

11:53.047 --> 11:55.508
(soft music playing
on headphones)

11:55.674 --> 11:57.510
It's Jack Hock.

11:57.593 --> 11:59.929
Last time I saw you...
Thank you.

12:00.012 --> 12:02.056
We were both pleasantly pissed

12:02.139 --> 12:03.599
at some horrible book party.

12:03.682 --> 12:04.682
Am I right?

12:04.767 --> 12:07.645
It's slowly flooding back to me.

12:07.728 --> 12:08.872
BARTENDER:
Hey, what can I get you?

12:08.896 --> 12:11.273
You're friends with,
um, Julia some...

12:11.357 --> 12:12.733
- Steinberg!
- Yeah.

12:12.900 --> 12:15.152
(sighs) She's not an
agent anymore. She died.

12:15.319 --> 12:17.446
She did? Jesus, that's young.

12:17.613 --> 12:19.323
Maybe she didn't die.

12:19.407 --> 12:21.867
Maybe she just moved back
to the suburbs.

12:21.951 --> 12:23.494
I always confuse those two.

12:23.577 --> 12:24.787
No, that's right.

12:24.870 --> 12:26.622
She got married and had twins.

12:26.705 --> 12:27.915
Better to have died.

12:28.082 --> 12:29.333
Indeed.

12:32.002 --> 12:33.421
(Jack exhales)

12:35.131 --> 12:36.891
I've just come from having
my teeth bleached.

12:36.966 --> 12:38.175
How do they look?

12:38.342 --> 12:39.927
Why would you do that?

12:40.010 --> 12:41.804
Oh, teeth are a dead giveaway.

12:42.721 --> 12:44.765
Okay.
Can I buy you a drink?

12:45.266 --> 12:46.809
Even though
you're the posh writer?

12:46.934 --> 12:48.477
Thank you.
(snaps fingers) Craigy?

12:48.561 --> 12:49.562
Top her up.
CRAIG: Yeah?

12:51.605 --> 12:53.566
You know,
I keep trying to remember

12:53.649 --> 12:56.235
that party that you mentioned.

12:56.318 --> 12:58.779
And something keeps
flashing in my head.

12:58.863 --> 12:59.989
I know something happened,

13:00.072 --> 13:02.491
but I can't seem
to put my finger on it.

13:02.575 --> 13:04.118
Bad shrimp?

13:04.952 --> 13:07.580
Jack Hock, you said, huh?
CRAIG: Here you go.

13:08.622 --> 13:11.375
That's me.
The renegade, the rebel.

13:11.459 --> 13:13.335
Jack Hock, big cock.

13:14.962 --> 13:16.338
I'm sure
it'll come back to me.

13:18.591 --> 13:21.135
How's old life
been treating you?

13:21.218 --> 13:22.470
I can honestly boast

13:22.553 --> 13:24.430
that I'm banned from
Crosby Street Booksellers.

13:27.766 --> 13:30.227
I'm banned from Duane Reade.

13:30.311 --> 13:31.979
All of them.

13:32.062 --> 13:34.023
I have a little
shoplifting problem.

13:34.106 --> 13:36.775
Well, it's all in the past,
but, uh...

13:36.859 --> 13:40.779
but for some reason,
I have a very memorable mug.

13:40.863 --> 13:42.490
And now I have to take a bus

13:42.573 --> 13:46.285
just to buy shampoo
and aspirin and stuff.

13:47.953 --> 13:52.249
I'm joking. Duane Reade's
not the only rodeo in town.

13:53.250 --> 13:54.585
You pissed in a closet.

13:54.668 --> 13:58.506
- I did what?
- You pissed in a closet.

13:59.507 --> 14:00.966
Now I remember.

14:01.050 --> 14:02.259
Nobody could stop talking

14:02.343 --> 14:04.053
about the handsome
English gentleman...

14:04.136 --> 14:05.136
Why, thank you.

14:05.262 --> 14:07.431
...who was so shit-faced

14:07.515 --> 14:10.601
he mistook the coat
closet for the can.

14:11.602 --> 14:13.896
You ruined thousands
of dollars' worth of furs.

14:13.979 --> 14:15.314
Well, I...

14:15.397 --> 14:20.152
Those old biddies didn't know
what hit 'em.

14:20.236 --> 14:22.780
(both laughing)

14:22.863 --> 14:26.534
Oh, their disgusting furs
covered in piss.

14:26.617 --> 14:28.953
Dogs followed them home.

14:29.036 --> 14:30.871
(both continue laughing)

14:36.001 --> 14:38.379
I'm glad somebody
found it amusing.

14:38.462 --> 14:41.423
Some folks stopped talking
to me after that night.

14:41.507 --> 14:44.176
Well, fuck 'em.
Cheers.

14:45.427 --> 14:46.427
(Lee chuckles)

14:48.639 --> 14:50.391
So, do you work, Jack Hock?

14:50.474 --> 14:51.850
Oh, this and that.

14:51.934 --> 14:53.060
Mostly that.

14:53.978 --> 14:56.105
I happen to have
some very nice cocaine,

14:56.188 --> 14:57.273
if you're interested.

14:57.356 --> 14:59.275
No, I'm not.

14:59.358 --> 15:01.238
Oh, Jesus, it's not like
I have it all the time.

15:01.277 --> 15:03.028
Boy's gotta do
what a boy's gotta do.

15:03.112 --> 15:05.322
Anyways, (sniffles)
who are you to judge?

15:05.406 --> 15:07.166
It's four in the afternoon,
and you're drunk.

15:07.366 --> 15:08.617
I'm hardly drunk.

15:08.742 --> 15:10.286
Mmm?

15:10.369 --> 15:12.871
It's not "anyways,"
it's "anyway."

15:13.914 --> 15:16.792
Anyways, let's keep drinking.

15:16.875 --> 15:17.876
The day is young.

15:18.043 --> 15:20.588
(jazz music playing)

15:25.134 --> 15:26.135
Hey!

15:31.056 --> 15:33.225
You getting off
at the next stop?

15:34.059 --> 15:36.604
79th. And you?

15:36.687 --> 15:38.272
Yeah, I'll get out there.

15:38.355 --> 15:39.898
Works for me.

15:39.982 --> 15:41.442
(indistinct radio chatter)

15:42.568 --> 15:44.403
I think I saw you
at Zabar's once.

15:44.486 --> 15:46.113
You were shouting at someone.

15:46.196 --> 15:48.657
They have terrible
customer service.

15:48.741 --> 15:50.743
I shopped there for years.

15:52.161 --> 15:54.455
They've really great bread.

16:01.879 --> 16:03.464
Oh, it's delicious.

16:04.798 --> 16:06.216
It's really good.

16:06.300 --> 16:07.885
So good.

16:07.968 --> 16:09.637
(dog barks)

16:09.720 --> 16:12.222
Oh, my.
That's the guy.

16:12.306 --> 16:13.307
JACK: Who?

16:13.599 --> 16:15.851
That's the asshole
from Crosby Street Bookseller.

16:15.934 --> 16:17.353
No.

16:17.519 --> 16:20.522
- What are the odds of that?
- Oh, I love the way you smell.

16:20.606 --> 16:21.732
(dog barking)

16:22.733 --> 16:24.860
Pen and paper.
Quick, quick, quick.

16:24.943 --> 16:26.028
Why?

16:28.489 --> 16:31.283
Come on.
I've got... Hang on. I...

16:44.838 --> 16:46.256
(dog barking)

16:48.175 --> 16:50.302
- Got it!
- LEE: Shh!

16:55.391 --> 16:56.558
(dog barks)

16:58.352 --> 17:00.270
This is me.

17:00.354 --> 17:01.563
Nice place.

17:01.647 --> 17:05.275
Used to be a lot nicer.
How about you?

17:05.358 --> 17:06.984
Couple of blocks along.

17:09.655 --> 17:10.781
Well...

17:12.574 --> 17:15.327
Jack, this was not unpleasant.

17:15.411 --> 17:17.037
See you tomorrow?

17:17.663 --> 17:18.872
You shall.

17:18.955 --> 17:20.624
(door opens)

18:38.744 --> 18:40.496
ANNA (reading):
<i>"Lee, today was to have been</i>

18:40.579 --> 18:42.247
<i>"the</i> Esquire <i>shoot with Spence.</i>

18:42.331 --> 18:44.500
"Difficult days, these.

18:44.583 --> 18:47.795
"Thank you for your sympathy
and understanding.

18:47.878 --> 18:49.797
"Ever yours, Kate.

18:49.880 --> 18:53.801
"P.S. Forgive the splotches.
All tears lately."

18:53.884 --> 18:57.054
(clicks tongue)
What a lovely apology.

18:58.764 --> 19:01.767
This is very special.
Why would you part with it?

19:02.476 --> 19:03.685
Clutter.

19:03.769 --> 19:05.938
You know, I'm not
a very sentimental gal.

19:06.021 --> 19:07.856
Handwritten even.

19:07.940 --> 19:09.525
You're the Lee Israel?

19:09.608 --> 19:11.652
Jesus, is there another one?

19:11.735 --> 19:14.154
I've read your biographies.

19:14.238 --> 19:16.365
- Have you?
- You're a wonderful writer.

19:16.448 --> 19:18.200
Thank you.

19:18.283 --> 19:20.702
You might want
to remind my publisher.

19:20.869 --> 19:22.871
Well, her letters usually have

19:22.955 --> 19:24.373
the intimacy of a phone book,

19:24.456 --> 19:27.084
but this one is really nice.

19:27.251 --> 19:29.920
How does $175 sound?

19:30.003 --> 19:31.839
Sounds terrific.

19:32.005 --> 19:34.091
(indistinct chatter)

19:35.300 --> 19:36.760
(cash register dings)

19:41.265 --> 19:44.059
I rang you.
You didn't ring me back.

19:44.142 --> 19:45.561
Should I take it personally?

19:45.686 --> 19:46.728
Well, why wouldn't you?

19:46.812 --> 19:48.132
(scoffs)
I'd never get out of bed.

19:48.188 --> 19:50.357
Then luckily for me, you did.

19:50.440 --> 19:52.109
I'm coming over to join you.

19:52.276 --> 19:55.445
I'm not good at reading
social cues.

19:56.697 --> 19:58.365
Uh, scotch and soda, Craig,

19:58.532 --> 20:01.076
- and I'll buy his next one.
- You got it.

20:01.159 --> 20:02.703
JACK:
Mmm, things are looking up.

20:02.786 --> 20:04.621
Aren't you writing a new book?

20:04.705 --> 20:05.706
About Fanny Brice.

20:05.873 --> 20:06.915
Who?

20:08.000 --> 20:09.376
Fanny Brice.

20:09.459 --> 20:11.753
Just the greatest vaudeville
comedian of her time.

20:13.338 --> 20:15.382
You sure you're a fag?

20:15.549 --> 20:17.426
Mm-hmm.

20:21.221 --> 20:23.223
(jazz music playing)

21:20.489 --> 21:22.032
(woman coughing)

21:32.584 --> 21:34.294
Hmm.

21:44.596 --> 21:47.849
Just recently found out
that my cousin, Sidney,

21:48.058 --> 21:51.395
was in possession of this
delightful bonne bouche.

21:51.478 --> 21:54.731
And I just thought that
you might be interested in it.

21:54.815 --> 21:58.026
Fanny Brice.
One of my favorites.

21:58.110 --> 21:59.945
I'm writing a new
biography about her.

22:00.028 --> 22:01.738
Well, what a funny
coincidence then,

22:01.822 --> 22:03.198
that your cousin had this.

22:05.659 --> 22:08.620
Didn't she say, "Wrong is for
other people"? I love that.

22:08.704 --> 22:10.455
She did say that.

22:13.792 --> 22:16.169
So, what do you think?

22:16.253 --> 22:17.796
I believe I can sell this.

22:17.879 --> 22:20.674
I could give you $75.

22:20.757 --> 22:22.259
Oh. Uh...

22:22.342 --> 22:24.302
I could give more
for better content.

22:24.386 --> 22:26.263
It's a bit bland is all.

22:26.346 --> 22:28.223
True.
(chuckles)

22:28.348 --> 22:30.726
Um, well, do you think
you could pay in cash?

22:30.809 --> 22:32.811
Oh. Let me see if I have enough.

22:33.812 --> 22:36.023
I'm glad to hear you're writing
another book.

22:36.106 --> 22:38.025
I'll be the first to buy it.

22:39.735 --> 22:42.029
Did you hear Tom Clancy
is getting paid

22:42.112 --> 22:43.238
three million dollars

22:43.405 --> 22:45.365
to write more right-wing
macho bullshit?

22:45.449 --> 22:46.867
Are you kidding me?

22:46.950 --> 22:49.244
That blowhard's getting
three million dollars?

22:49.327 --> 22:50.787
(scoffs)
Oh, to be a white male

22:50.871 --> 22:53.331
that doesn't even know
he's full of crap, right?

22:53.498 --> 22:57.169
I've tried to write a little.
Short stories.

22:57.252 --> 22:59.713
I know better than to presume
they're any good.

22:59.796 --> 23:02.466
Oh, I can't believe
I just admitted that.

23:02.549 --> 23:04.009
I'm sure they're terrible.

23:04.176 --> 23:05.886
They might be.

23:07.304 --> 23:09.306
Or they might not be.

23:09.389 --> 23:10.891
You know, I could take a look.

23:12.142 --> 23:13.226
Really?

23:13.310 --> 23:15.187
